    '1. Preheat oven to 325°F. Toss beef with salt, pepper, and flour.

2. Heat oil in a Dutch oven over medium-high. Brown beef in batches, 3-4 minutes per side. Remove.

3. Reduce heat. Sauté onion 5 minutes until soft. Add garlic and tomato paste; cook 1 minute.

4. Pour in wine, scraping up any fond. Reduce 2 minutes.

5. Return beef. Add broth, bay leaves, and thyme. Bring to a simmer, cover, and braise in the oven 90 minutes.

